            <td valign="top" width="53%"> <b>Summary:</b>
            <p>The Longhorn Array Database (LAD) is a MIAME compliant
microarray database that operates on <b> <a
 href="http://www.postgresql.org" target="_blank">PostgreSQL</a></b>
and <b><a href="http://www.linux.org" target="_blank">Linux</a></b>. </p>
            <p>It is a fully open source version of the <b> <a
 href="http://genome-www5.stanford.edu/MicroArray/SMD/" target="_blank">Stanford
Microarray Database</a></b> (SMD), one of the largest microarray
databases.</p>
            <p>LAD provides a simple, free, open, reliable and proven
solution for storage and analysis of two-color microarray data.</p>
            <p>LAD stores raw and normalized data from microarray
experiments, as well as their corresponding image files.&nbsp; In
addition, LAD provides interfaces for data retrieval, analysis, and
visualization.</p>
            <p><b><br>
Availability:</b></p>
            <p>Use the links above to <b><a href="download.html">download</a></b>
the new version 1.5 package or read the <b><a href="install.html">installation</a></b>
instructions.</p>
